instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The described Digital Twin framework relies on several established standards. Structural and behavioural models are expressed with SysML (an OMG standard) and with architecture description languages such as ACME, AADL (SAE standard) and MontiArc, which are referenced in Document 1. Data exchange between physical assets and the twin can use the MQTT protocol, for which an open‑source implementation (Mosquitto) is cited in Document 6, indicating compliance with the OASIS MQTT standard. The processing component model references simulation and data‑calculation models that may be executed in tools such as MathWorks Simulink, a de‑facto industry standard for dynamic system modelling (Document 1). No explicit certification or conformity assessment procedures are mentioned."
]
